{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP is the dominant boundary: whether the draft actually grounds itself in thread details depends on real model behavior and prompt adherence, which can vary run to run. A mocked or deterministic generator would hide generic-response failures (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Run the real drafting model on a representative set of real email threads and assert the reply includes concrete thread-specific references (for example named project items, dates, or explicit asks) instead of only boilerplate language; evaluate with a rubric over multiple runs to catch non-deterministic generic outputs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is mainly at module handoff boundaries (claim extraction -> KB lookup -> contradiction decision), not a single pure function (MOCK-MISS). No real external infra is strictly required if KB is local. This can be caught with real local components wired together.","test_description":"Use a local KB fixture and real contradiction-check pipeline modules end-to-end (no mocks of extractor/checker). Feed drafts containing known contradictory claims and verify the checker returns flags tied to the conflicting KB entries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.52,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Even with correct wiring, the key risk is model behavior under missing evidence: real LLMs may hallucinate or omit disclaimers (LLM-DEP). Mocked generation would systematically miss this failure (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Execute real draft generation with empty/irrelevant KB retrieval results across multiple realistic threads; verify the draft contains the required uncertainty disclaimer and does not assert unsupported concrete facts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a local workflow-state and module-interaction boundary (draft state machine, approval gate, send dispatcher). Unit tests of a single function can miss wiring/order bugs; real external email infra is not required to catch the core failure.","test_description":"Wire real local workflow components with a test double outbox at the send boundary; simulate draft creation and fact-check completion without approval and assert zero send events, then approve and assert exactly one send event.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior is explicitly a full pipeline validation across sequential stages and includes at least one real agentic stage (draft generation). The real failure boundary is orchestration across the whole agent flow, not any single step.","test_description":"Run the production-like pipeline on a real email thread fixture: ingest thread, call real drafting model, run factual check against KB, and verify the system presents an approval-required draft artifact. Assert stage outputs and transitions across the full chain.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.7}}]}
